===Pronunciation===

:feld' spär, fel' spär

===Etymology===

:Feld, field (from Middle High German veld, from Old High German feld) + Spath, spar

===noun===
#A large group of rock-forming [[mineral]]s that, together, make up about 60% of the earth's outer [[crust]]. The feldspars are all [[aluminum]] [[silicate]]s of the [[alkalai]] metals ''[[sodium]], [[potassium]], [[calcium]] and [[barium]]''. Feldspars are the principal constituents of [[igneous]] and [[plutonic]] rocks.


